    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I came here looking for the best way to do this, but then decided to go with:</p>\n<pre><code>String.valueOf(&lt;your-int&gt;).getBytes()\n</code></pre>\n<p>It was simpler for my purposes (writing an int to a file). Not to mention that when encoding you can use less than 4 bytes for small values (ascii) vs. encoding a 32-bit int.</p>\n"
